---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Intelligence for B2B startups and scaleups"
  description="Build an evidence-backed startup story, test it against customer learning and strengthen the position as your company grows."
  ogDescription="Editorial Intelligence helps B2B startups build their first credible story and scaleups turn accumulated evidence into a position their market can recognise."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="ss-inner">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">Application</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">Editorial Intelligence for B2B startups and scaleups</h1>
        <p class="ss-lead mb-8">Build the first credible story. Then strengthen it as the evidence grows.</p>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Every startup begins with a conviction: that a problem matters, that the market has misunderstood it or that there is a better way to solve it.</p>
          <p>But conviction alone is not a position.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence connects founder experience, customer discovery, product decisions and market signals to build an evidence-backed story the company can test. As the organisation grows, the same approach helps it connect accumulating knowledge into a position the market can recognise.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="ss-btn">Discuss your startup's story</a>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Opening distinction -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-6">A story grounded in what you are learning</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-6">
          <p>Startup storytelling is often treated as an exercise in finding more compelling language.</p>
          <p>The more important work comes before the language: determining what the company genuinely believes, which parts of its interpretation are distinctive, what current evidence supports it and which assumptions still need to be tested.</p>
          <p>That creates a story grounded in reality rather than a polished version of the founder's hopes.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="ss-qualifier">This work becomes useful once a startup has more than an idea: founder conviction, early customer learning and a market hypothesis worth testing.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Stage model -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-10">The narrative problem changes as the company grows</h2>
        <div class="stages-grid">

          <div class="stage-card">
            <div class="stage-header">
              <span class="stage-num">01</span>
              <div>
                <p class="stage-label">Early startup</p>
                <h3 class="stage-heading">Build the position</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-body">
              <div class="stage-section">
                <p class="stage-section-label">Narrative problem</p>
                <p class="stage-text">The company has strong founder conviction and an emerging product, but its understanding of the problem is still developing.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="stage-section">
                <p class="stage-section-label">Editorial Intelligence role</p>
                <p class="stage-text">Connect founder experience, early customer discovery and market signals into an initial strategic argument. Separate what is known from what is assumed and identify what needs to be tested next.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="stage-card">
            <div class="stage-header">
              <span class="stage-num">02</span>
              <div>
                <p class="stage-label">Growing startup</p>
                <h3 class="stage-heading">Test and connect the story</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-body">
              <div class="stage-section">
                <p class="stage-section-label">Narrative problem</p>
                <p class="stage-text">Customer conversations, sales objections and product learning are accumulating, but they do not always support the story in the same way.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="stage-section">
                <p class="stage-section-label">Editorial Intelligence role</p>
                <p class="stage-text">Compare the emerging evidence with the original narrative, identify patterns and contradictions, and evolve the position without losing its distinctive core.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="stage-card">
            <div class="stage-header">
              <span class="stage-num">03</span>
              <div>
                <p class="stage-label">Scaleup</p>
                <h3 class="stage-heading">Organise and compound the evidence</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-body">
              <div class="stage-section">
                <p class="stage-section-label">Narrative problem</p>
                <p class="stage-text">The company possesses substantial customer and market knowledge, but it is fragmented across teams, systems, assets and individuals.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="stage-section">
                <p class="stage-section-label">Editorial Intelligence role</p>
                <p class="stage-text">Connect accumulated evidence into a recognisable position, thought leadership platform and editorial system that can develop over time.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Early-stage -->
      <section id="early-stage" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-6">Build the first evidence-backed narrative</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>For an early-stage startup, the evidence may not yet consist of large research studies or hundreds of customer stories.</p>
          <p>It may come from the founder's lived experience, early customer interviews, product decisions, sales conversations and the market conditions that prompted the company to exist.</p>
          <p>The task is to determine what those signals add up to without pretending that early assumptions are established facts.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="ss-h3 mb-4">The work can include</h3>
        <ul class="ss-list mb-8">
          <li>Founder interviews and existing-material review</li>
          <li>Analysis of customer discovery and early sales conversations</li>
          <li>Review of category language and competing narratives</li>
          <li>Separation of evidence, assumptions and unresolved questions</li>
          <li>Definition of the problem the company believes the market has misunderstood</li>
          <li>Development of the core argument and narrative structure</li>
          <li>Identification of founder thought leadership territories</li>
          <li>A plan for testing and strengthening the narrative</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="ss-h3 mb-3">What you leave with</h3>
        <p class="ss-outcome mb-8">A clear strategic argument, a narrative and messaging foundation, an evidence-versus-assumption map and a practical plan for validating the story through future customer learning.</p>

        <div class="named-engagement">
          <p class="named-engagement-title">Startup narrative foundation</p>
          <p class="named-engagement-desc">A focused engagement for founders who need to clarify what the company stands for before investing heavily in content, thought leadership or wider communications.</p>
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="ss-link">Discuss a startup narrative foundation →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Growing startup -->
      <section id="growing-startup" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-6">Let customer learning change the story</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>As a startup begins selling and delivering its product, the market starts answering back.</p>
          <p>Customers may describe the problem differently from the founder. Sales conversations may expose a stronger motivation. Product decisions may reveal that the company's real value lies somewhere unexpected.</p>
          <p>This is where the original story should be tested rather than protected.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="ss-h3 mb-4">The work can include</h3>
        <ul class="ss-list mb-8">
          <li>Connecting customer interviews, sales insight and product learning</li>
          <li>Identifying recurring language, needs and objections</li>
          <li>Comparing the evidence with the company's existing positioning</li>
          <li>Finding tensions between the founder story and customer reality</li>
          <li>Refining the strategic argument</li>
          <li>Identifying new questions for customer discovery</li>
          <li>Establishing a repeatable signal-capture process</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="ss-h3 mb-3">What you leave with</h3>
        <p class="ss-outcome">An evolved position grounded in customer learning, clearer shared language across the company and a system for continuing to test the narrative as new evidence appears.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Scaleup -->
      <section id="scaleup" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-6">Turn accumulated knowledge into market authority</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Scaleups often know much more than their positioning shows.</p>
          <p>Founder expertise, customer stories, research, webinars, events, sales feedback and product knowledge become distributed across departments and systems. The organisation grows more knowledgeable while finding it harder to see what it collectively knows.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence creates the narrative layer across that evidence.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="ss-h3 mb-4">The work can include</h3>
        <ul class="ss-list mb-8">
          <li>Narrative audits</li>
          <li>Customer-evidence synthesis</li>
          <li>Research activation</li>
          <li>Founder and executive thought leadership architecture</li>
          <li>Webinar and event intelligence</li>
          <li>Category and market positioning</li>
          <li>Organisational evidence systems</li>
          <li>Ongoing Editorial Intelligence advisory</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="ss-h3 mb-3">What you leave with</h3>
        <p class="ss-outcome">A distinctive strategic position, the evidence supporting it and an editorial architecture through which the organisation can build authority consistently.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Shared applications -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-8">Where Editorial Intelligence can help</h2>
        <div class="shared-apps-grid">

          <div class="shared-app-card">
            <h3 class="shared-app-title">Founder thought leadership</h3>
            <p class="shared-app-desc">Turn founder experience, informed opinions and emerging market insight into a coherent position rather than a stream of disconnected posts.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="shared-app-card">
            <h3 class="shared-app-title">Customer discovery</h3>
            <p class="shared-app-desc">Treat interviews and sales conversations as evidence that can challenge and strengthen the company's story.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="shared-app-card">
            <h3 class="shared-app-title">Category positioning</h3>
            <p class="shared-app-desc">Define the market problem the company can credibly own and the distinctive interpretation it brings to that problem.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="shared-app-card">
            <h3 class="shared-app-title">Research activation</h3>
            <p class="shared-app-desc">Turn proprietary data or commissioned research into an argument that can support sustained thought leadership.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="shared-app-card">
            <h3 class="shared-app-title">Webinar and event intelligence</h3>
            <p class="shared-app-desc">Extract themes, questions, tensions and market signals from webinars, roundtables, conferences and customer events.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="shared-app-card">
            <h3 class="shared-app-title">Organisational memory</h3>
            <p class="shared-app-desc">Prevent important customer and market learning from disappearing across Slack, Notion, call recordings, decks and individual employees.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What this is not -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-6">More than startup storytelling</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>This is not a service for inventing a more exciting origin story or making unsupported claims sound persuasive.</p>
          <p>It is not outsourced social content, brand naming, pitch-deck design or a substitute for customer discovery.</p>
          <p>The purpose is to create a stronger connection between what the company says and what it is genuinely learning.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Who this is for -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-6">Who this work is suited to</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>This work is designed for B2B startups and scaleups operating in complex, technical, regulated or rapidly changing markets, where credibility depends on genuine expertise.</p>
          <p>That may include fintech, accounting technology, SaaS, AI, future of work, professional services and other emerging categories.</p>
        </div>
        <h3 class="ss-h3 mb-4">It is most useful for</h3>
        <ul class="ss-list mb-8">
          <li>Founders preparing to articulate a clearer market position</li>
          <li>Marketing and content leaders who need stronger strategic foundations</li>
          <li>Scaleup leadership teams whose accumulated knowledge has become fragmented</li>
          <li>Companies preparing to invest in thought leadership, research or a larger content programme</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="ss-qualifier">It is less useful for companies that have not yet spoken to prospective customers or developed a meaningful hypothesis about the problem they want to solve.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Ways to start -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-8">Ways to start</h2>
        <div class="ways-grid">

          <div class="way-card way-card--primary">
            <h3 class="way-title">Startup narrative foundation</h3>
            <p class="way-desc">Build an initial evidence-backed story from founder conviction, customer discovery and market signals.</p>
            <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="ss-btn way-cta">Discuss a startup narrative foundation</a>
          </div>

          <div class="way-card">
            <h3 class="way-title">Narrative audit</h3>
            <p class="way-desc">Review the research, customer insight, founder thinking and market evidence the company has already accumulated.</p>
            <a href="/work#services" class="ss-link way-cta-link">Explore the narrative audit →</a>
          </div>

          <div class="way-card">
            <h3 class="way-title">Thought leadership architecture</h3>
            <p class="way-desc">Turn organisational expertise into a distinctive position supported by evidence and proprietary ideas.</p>
            <a href="/work#services" class="ss-link way-cta-link">Explore thought leadership architecture →</a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Closing CTA -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="ss-h2 mb-6">What does your company know that its story does not yet show?</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Tell me what prompted the company, what you are hearing from customers and where the existing story feels incomplete. I'll help you determine whether there is a stronger position inside it — and what evidence is needed to develop it.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=Editorial%20Intelligence%20project%20enquiry" class="ss-btn mb-4 inline-flex">Discuss your startup's story</a>
        <p class="ss-email-alt"><a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co" class="ss-email-link">asavin@editorialintelligence.co</a></p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ss-inner {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  /* ── Typography ── */
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .ss-lead {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.3rem);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .ss-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.35rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .ss-h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
  }

  .ss-qualifier {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-rule);
  }

  .ss-outcome {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  /* ── List ── */
  .ss-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.65rem;
  }

  .ss-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .ss-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }

  /* ── Buttons and links ── */
  .ss-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-surface);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .ss-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

  .ss-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .ss-link:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); }

  .ss-email-alt {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ss-email-link {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .ss-email-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  /* ── Stage model ── */
  .stages-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .stages-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .stage-card {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .stage-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.875rem;
  }

  .stage-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .stage-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .stage-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .stage-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .stage-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .stage-section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .stage-text {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Named engagement ── */
  .named-engagement {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .named-engagement-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .named-engagement-desc {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem 0;
  }

  /* ── Shared applications ── */
  .shared-apps-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  @media (min-width: 560px) {
    .shared-apps-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .shared-app-card {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .shared-app-title {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .shared-app-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Ways to start ── */
  .ways-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .way-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .way-card--primary {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, var(--color-rule));
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 4%, var(--color-surface-secondary));
  }

  .way-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .way-desc {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 0.375rem 0;
  }

  .way-cta {
    align-self: flex-start;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .way-cta-link {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    align-self: flex-start;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .way-cta-link:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); }

  .mb-4 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .inline-flex { display: inline-flex; }
</style>
